### Brute Force
> Could we break the word? We can start from putting the first space.
> Where should we put the first space? We can enumerate all possible positions to put the first space.

> Take `s = leetcodegood, wordDict = {leet, code, good}` for example,
 ```
   leetcodegood______________________________________________________________________________________
	 /                \                     \                \  leet in dict                        \ 
l(eetcodegood) le(etcodegood) lee(tcodegood)     leet(codegood)________________                      leetc(odegood) ...
                                                  /           |        \         \ code in dict
                                              c(odegood) co(degood) cod(egood) code(good)
                                                                                /
                                                                              g(ood), ...
 ```
> We check all possible break positions 'l', 'le', 'lee'... until we meet `leet`, which is in dict.
> Then the problem becomes to if we could break `codegood`, etc.
```
class Solution {
    public boolean wordBreak(String s, List<String> wordDict) {
        return recur(s, 0, wordDict);
    }

    private boolean recur(String s, int curIndex, List<String> wordDict) {
        if (curIndex == s.length()) {
            return true;
        }

        for (int end = curIndex + 1; end <= s.length(); end++) {
            String split = s.substring(curIndex, end);
            if (wordDict.contains(split)) {
                if(recur(s, end, wordDict)) {
                    return true;
                }
            }
        }

        return false;
    }
}
```


### Top-down DP
We can use memoization to overcome overlapping subproblems.
```
class Solution {
    private Boolean[] dp;
    public boolean wordBreak(String s, List<String> wordDict) {
        dp = new Boolean[s.length()];
        return recur(s, 0, wordDict);
    }


    private boolean recur(String s, int curIndex, List<String> wordDict) {
        if (curIndex == s.length()) {
            return true;
        }

        if (dp[curIndex] != null) {
            return dp[curIndex];
        }
        for (int end = curIndex + 1; end <= s.length(); end++) {
            String split = s.substring(curIndex, end);
            if (wordDict.contains(split)) {
                if(recur(s, end, wordDict)) {
                    return dp[curIndex] = true;
                }
            }
        }

        return dp[curIndex] = false;
    }
}
```
### Bottom-up DP
Define dp[i] as whether we can break s[0, i).
```
class Solution {
    public boolean wordBreak(String s, List<String> wordDict) {
        Set<String> wordSet = new HashSet<>();
        wordSet.addAll(wordDict);

        boolean[] dp = new boolean[s.length() + 1];
        dp[0] = true;
        for (int i = 1; i < dp.length ; i++) {
            for (int k = 1; k <= i; k++) {
                dp[i] = dp[i] || (dp[i - k] && wordSet.contains(s.substring(i - k, i)));
            }
        }
        return dp[s.length()];
    }
}
```

