# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Break the problem into subproblems sb and check if sb can be segmented into a space-separated sequence of one or more dictionary words.

For detailed explanation you can refer to my youtube channel (Hindi Language)
https://youtu.be/-bSiawDmYkQ
 or link in my profile.Here,you can find any solution in playlists monthwise from June 2023 with detailed explanation.i upload daily leetcode solution video with short and precise explanation (5-10) minutes.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
The code uses a recursive approach with memoization to determine if the input string `s` can be broken down into valid words from the given `wordDict`. It iterates through all possible prefixes of the input string, and for each prefix, it checks if it exists in the `wordDict`. If found, it makes a recursive call with the remaining suffix of the input string. Memoization is used to avoid redundant computations and improve efficiency. If a valid segmentation is found, the function returns `true`, otherwise `false`.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:$$O(n*n)$$ where n is string length.
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:$$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

