```

Now, what will be the base case...

Let us say after **incrementing the index "i"**, you reach the end of the string..**It means you were able to find all the combinations**..**so return a true...**

```
  if(i==s.size())
    {
        return true;
    }
```

Now, how do i memoize it...The ans is simple...

We know that , **only a single index "i" is changing**...so we will make a **1-d dp array** and **store 1 or 0**, if it is true we will **store 1 and if false , we will store a 0 in the dp array...**

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
We are making a 1-d dp array and we are just iterating the string given to us so...**O(N)**

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
We made a 1-d dp array and a hash map , where the hashmap stores all the strings so it will be **O(N +M)**, where M will be the no of strings presnt in the array...

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:


    bool check(int i,string &s,unordered_map<string,int>&jd, vector<int>&dp)
    {

