solutions.content:
* Break the string if the first part of it is in the set of dictionary words
* Check that the rest of the string can be also broken into dictionary words by doing a recursive call
* This is divide and concur.
* There are overlapping subproblems so memoize
```
class Solution {
    Set<String> set;
    Map<String, Boolean> map;
    public boolean wordBreak(String s, List<String> wordDict) {
        set = new HashSet<>(wordDict);
        map = new HashMap<>();

        return check(s);
    }

    public boolean check(String s) {
        if(s.length() == 0 || set.contains(s)) return true;
        if(map.containsKey(s)) return map.get(s);
        for(int i = 1; i <= s.length() - 1; i++) {
            if(set.contains(s.substring(0, i)) && check(s.substring(i))) {
                map.put(s, true);
                return true;
            }
        }
        map.put(s, false);
        return false;
    }
}
```

