solutions.content:
[🎨 The ART of Dynamic Programming:](https://leetcode.com/discuss/general-discussion/712010/The-ART-of-Dynamic-Programming-An-Intuitive-Approach%3A-from-Apprentice-to-Master)

1. **A**ll possibilities are considered via top-down brute-force depth-first-search
2. **R**emember each subproblem's optimal solution via a DP memo
3. **T**urn the top-down solution upside-down to create the bottom-up solution

---

**Top-Down:** Recursively `go()` explore each `i`<sup>th</sup> index of the input string `s` as a subproblem with the goal of reaching `N`, the cardinality of `s`.  The base case occurs when `i == N`, ie. we can reach the empty string without having to do anything, so we can return `true`.  Then we see if each candidate `cand` substring `s[i..j)` (from `i` inclusive to `j` non-inclusive) has been `seen` in the input array `A`.  If so, then we recursively explore the `j`<sup>th</sup> subproblem.  As the recursive stack unwinds, each `i`<sup>th</sup> subproblem is set to `true` if and only if the candidate `cand` substring `s[i..j)` has been `seen` and the `j`<sup>th</sup> subproblem was also previously set to `true`, ie. we are attempting to "append" each candidate `cand` substring `s[i..j)` onto previously found `j`<sup>th</sup> subproblem solutions.

**Bottom-Up:** Let `dp[i]` denote the `i`<sup>th</sup> index of the input string `s` is reachable.  Explicitly set the base case `dp[N] = true` to denote the empty string is reachable.  Then iteratively explore each candidate `cand` substring `s[i..j)` attempting to build upon each previously found `j`<sup>th</sup> subproblem solution to mimic the recursive stack unwinding from `i = N - 1..0` inclusive.

---

**Kotlin Solutions:**
1. **A**ll possibilities are considered via top-down brute-force depth-first-search
```
class Solution {
    fun wordBreak(s: String, A: List<String>): Boolean {
        var N = s.length
        var seen = A.toSet()
        fun go(i: Int = 0): Boolean {
            if (i == N)
                return true
            for (j in i + 1..N) {
                var cand = s.substring(i, j)
                if (seen.contains(cand) && go(j))
                    return true
            }
            return false
        }
        return go()
    }
}
```

2. **R**emember each subproblem's optimal solution via a DP memo
```
class Solution {
    fun wordBreak(s: String, A: List<String>): Boolean {
        var N = s.length
        var seen = A.toSet()
        var m = mutableMapOf<Int, Boolean>()
        fun go(i: Int = 0): Boolean {
            if (i == N)
                return true
            if (!m.contains(i)) {
                m[i] = false
                for (j in i + 1..N) {
                    var cand = s.substring(i, j)
                    if (seen.contains(cand) && go(j))
                        m[i] = true
                }
            }
            return m[i]!!
        }
        return go()
    }
}
```

3. **T**urn the top-down solution upside-down to create the bottom-up solution
```
class Solution {
    fun wordBreak(s: String, A: List<String>): Boolean {
        var N = s.length
        var seen = A.toSet()
        var dp = BooleanArray(N + 1) { false }
        dp[N] = true
        for (i in N - 1 downTo 0) {
            for (j in i + 1..N) {
                if (!dp[j])
                    continue
                var cand = s.substring(i, j)
                if (seen.contains(cand))
                    dp[i] = true
            }
        }
        return dp[0]
    }
}
```

