# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Intuition behind this problem was to search for a possible dictionary word at every index. For this purpose, a map was created with a vector of strings for the letter they start with.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
At every index, if substring was found matching a dictionary word, the same thing is continued until the end of the string was reached.
The dp stores whether a set of words from dictionary can be fused to complete the string from a particular index till the end of string.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
