A more efficient approach would be to use dynamic programming (DP) where you'd keep track of whether each substring of 's' can be broken down into words from wordDict. You could use a boolean DP array where `dp[i]` represents whether the substring `s[0...i]` can be broken down into words from the dictionary. This way, you avoid repeated computation and reduce the time complexity significantly.

Here's a sample implementation of this approach:

