# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Since the query is on static data (i.e. **nums** array is not changing), we can use Sparse table for _Constant time_ Query.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
In sparse table we precompute values of all subarrays of size $$2^j$$ where $$j$$ varies from 0 to logN.

Create a sparse table for $$max$$ type query.

https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/sparse-table/

$$Note:$$  
- This concept can alse be used for **min**  and **gcd** query over the given range.
- Can be solved using **Segment tree**.

# Query function explaination
Find highest power of 2 that is smaller than or equal to count of elements in given range.

_For [2, 10], j = 3_  

# Complexity
- Time complexity:$$O(N*logN + N)$$
    - $$O(N*logN)$$  to build Sparse table and $$O(N)$$ for query

- Space complexity: $$O(N*logN)$$

# Code
```
class Solution {
private:
    // SPARSE TABLE
    int sparse[100005][30];
    // Size of sparse table N X log N
    void buildSparseTable(int n,vector<int>& nums) {
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) 
            sparse[i][0] = nums[i]; 

        for (int j = 1; (1 << j) <= n; j++) { 
            for (int i = 0; (i + (1 << j) - 1) < n; i++){
                sparse[i][j] = max(sparse[i][j - 1], 
                            sparse[i + (1 << (j - 1))][j - 1]);
            } 
        } 
    }
    int query(int L, int R) { 
        int len = R - L + 1;
        int j = (int)log2(len); 
        return max(sparse[L][j], sparse[R - (1 << j) + 1][j]);
    }

public:
    vector<int> maxSlidingWindow(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        int n = nums.size();
        buildSparseTable(n,nums);

        vector<int> res;
        for(int i=0;i+k<=n;i++)
            res.push_back(query(i,i+k-1));

        return res;        
    }
};
```

