solutions.content:
### O(nlogk) time, O(k) space
> With constant space, the solution takes O(nk) time, where k counts for finding the maximum of a window.

> To raise k to logk, we take advantage of a self-balancing binary search tree: TreeMap in Java is such an implementation.
```
    public int[] maxSlidingWindow(int[] nums, int k) {
        if (nums.length == 0) {
            return new int[0];
        }
        int[] res = new int[nums.length - k + 1];
        TreeMap<Integer, Integer> window = new TreeMap<>();

        for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
            if (i - k + 1 > 0) {
                // remove leftmost indexed in window, i - k
                window.put(nums[i - k], window.get(nums[i - k]) - 1);
                if (window.get(nums[i - k]) == 0) {
                    window.remove(nums[i - k]);
                }
            }
            window.put(nums[i], window.getOrDefault(nums[i], 0) + 1);
            if (i - k + 1 >= 0) {
                res[i - k + 1] = window.lastKey();
            }
        }

        return res;
    }
```
### O(n) time, O(k) space
> We maintain a deque of indices that their corresponding elements are possible to be the maximum of the current or future window

> It respects the contract that
> - indexes in deque are all in the current window 
> - their corresponding values are in decreasing order

> In this way, `deque.peekFirst` is always the maximal of current window

****
```
class Solution {
    public int[] maxSlidingWindow(int[] nums, int k) {
        Deque<Integer> monoDeq = new LinkedList<>();
        int[] resArr = new int[nums.length - k + 1];

        for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
            while (!monoDeq.isEmpty() && nums[monoDeq.getLast()] <= nums[i]) {
                monoDeq.removeLast();
            }
            monoDeq.addLast(i);
            if (monoDeq.getFirst() < i - k + 1) {
                monoDeq.removeFirst();
            }
            if (i - k + 1 >= 0) {
                resArr[i - k + 1] = nums[monoDeq.getFirst()];
            }
        }

        return resArr;
    }
}
