# Approach
 We are using the sliding window approach , in which we are moving from left to right and we are using the deque to track the maximum num present in the window . 
We are pushing and popping the elements from last because we are trying to make deque in the decreasing order so that maximum element can be obtained from the front of the deque .


# Complexity
- Time complexity:
- O(N)
- 

- Space complexity:
 O(K) // as the window can have max of k elements

