# Intuition
Using the automatic sorting property of ordered hashmaps.

# Approach
1) Declare an ordered map
2) Using 2 pointers i and j, traverse through the array and keep on inserting the elements in the map (the count of the element being the value in key-value pair)
3) Find the value of the maximum element by pointing the iterator to the end by mpp.end() and then it--
4) Keep on pushing the maximum element in the vector and remove the frequency of the element from the map.
5) Check (for repeating elements) if the frequency of any element is 0 then erase it from the map.
# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> maxSlidingWindow(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        map<int,int> mpp;
        vector<int> v;
        int i=0;
        int j=0;
        map<int,int> :: iterator it;
        while(j<nums.size()){
            mpp[nums[j]]++;
            if(j-i+1<k){
                j++;
            }
            else if(j-i+1==k){
                it=mpp.end();
                it--;
                v.push_back(it->first);
                //if(nums[i]==it->first){
                    mpp[nums[i]]--;
                //}
                if(mpp[nums[i]]==0) mpp.erase(nums[i]);
                i++;
                j++;
            }
        }
        return v;
    }
};
```

